wow, ltcmdrData you also have it wrong. Socialism is something like a republican or liberal system.  All it refers to is building or enhancing social services such as hospitals, transport, community services, and has nothing to do with political party systems other then the policies of the party involved.

Communism is a one party system which dictates what rules the system will follow. It may allow other parties into the government but it will have full dominance or this system will fail.

And democracy on the other hand allows a multi-party system to operate. 

Therefor you can have a socialist communist state, which the USSR claimed to be but blatantly was not, as well as socialist democratic parties, which dominate canada and most of the european states, or in the USA is very loosely represented by the democrats. This is mostly because anyone who claims to be a socialist in the USA is automatically called a Nazi or Communist due to the 'name' association during WWII and cold war era.
